<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-05-22T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-05-22T10:00:00-05:00" n="393" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d393">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/233: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ives</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-05-22T16:00:00+01:00">May 22, 1930—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 22—2:15 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>26. Department’s 25, May 19, 5 p.m. Danish note May 14 mentioned only
                            customs and tobacco revenues.</p>
                        <p>In a further note, dated May 20, Foreign Office states that by
                            declaration of Leith-Ross, dated April 16, last, Denmark has renounced
                            its liens on the revenues of the Austrian Government derived from the
                            customs and tobacco monopoly as well as such of the other revenues as
                            may from time to time be required as guarantee in favor of the creditors
                            of the new loan.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ives</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
